Create Custom Context Variables

Context variables for the contact are included, but you can create any type of context variable to use in your bot implementation. Use context variables for product names, store locations, referral URLs, or items in a customerâ€™s shopping cart.

Einstein Bots is available in Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience. Setup for Einstein Bots is available in Lightning Experience.
Available in: Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions

To build and manage Einstein Bots:
  - Customize Application
  - Modify Metadata
  - Manage Bots

Custom context variables can be linked to multiple channels and objects. The Chat channel can map to the LiveChatTranscript object and the Messaging Channels can map from either the MessagingSession or MessagingUser objects.

Start with a deactivated bot. If your bot is active, click Deactivate.
In the Bot Builder menu, select Variables.
To create a variable, click New. Set the type to Context and give it a name and Data Type. Save your changes.
Custom context variables must have a Data Type of Text, Number, or ID.

To map a custom context variable:
  - Click the variable name
  - Select Channel and Field
  - Save changes

The mapping shows with the channel and the API name of the mapped field.
title: Creating Custom Context Variables in Einstein Bots
